content: The app does what it says it does. And it's pretty much the only decoder I I could find. But as other users have said this app would be heaps better if it was able to interface with tasker via system broadcasts or even if it just outputted to a log file. When you lock the screen the mic stops listening so I could need a way to run in the background hence why a tasker plugin makes more sense.. I had a few numbers register multi times when I had only generated the DTMF sound once..
This app simply does NOT work for use with your own smartphone !

Nice app, UI is a little outdated but it does as advertised. If it integrated with tasker or at least made some sort of system broadcast when DTMF tones were recieved it would be amazing. Especially if it could be done in the background and dtmf macros could be triggered by tasker or shortcut. Lots of potential in this app
Absolutely does not send tones through phone... Useless to interface with remote boxes
I thought it would record tones played during a conversation 8
quality dtmf app

Probably the best DTMF app on the market here. I've been using it for over a year now and it has come in handy for several projects that require generating and decoding DTMF tones. Would be cool if the designers upgraded it with some extra features. I own several other apps made by Wolphi LLC and they all perform flawlessly.
Very high accuracy in decoding tones, top notch. Better then any other app on the market. Highly recommend. Money well spend.

Please make it run in the background too.  I recorded a series of DTMF tones with the builtin Voice Recorder and then play it back while this Receives goes in the background.. and it didn't catch it. I want to build a small automation to start my car remotely and for that I need this app to listen (in the background) non stop and a way (API) to read and clear the receive buffer from another app (that I will create). Or simply add a 'passworded relays automation' feature where the opto-link between the phone and the external relays is made by lighting/displaying some 1cm radius circles on a black screen
This is a very useful app to have in your phone.
other apps have choppy dtmf on my s4 . You can adjust tone lenght and pause. the dtmf decoder is not right thouht.  I can trigger dtmf with wistle
Great App    +    IT WORKS.
Great app, smart and easy to use with more than 90% accurate
Should add ability to add a number from address book
After others failed, this one worked.
Out of all the dtmf decoder apps I've tried, this one actually works.
Great App
Keep up the great work!
Works excelent.

* Does not allow copy-paste (via long-press or any other method), e.g. to paste in a long number for playback, from another app.  * Crashes when, in playback mode, the Clear button is pressed while playing back a long macro. I can reproduce this bug, but not 100% of the time: it seems to occur when Clear is pressed while the display is being updated with the current digit.
Perfect to the task.
Bin von dieser App begeistert,benutze es beruflich und es erleichtert mir das Testen ungemein!
EXCELLENT!!! Decoder works great on Samsung Galaxy Nexus (Sprint) and sending dtmf tones has loud enough  volume.

Fantastic, reliable DTMF decoding. On my LG Optimus V the encoder output volume is next to silent unless a headset is momentarily plugged into the phone after which everything works fine.  My only suggestion for improvement aside from the playback volume issue for my phone is to include the ability to trigger an alarm if a predetermined tone sequence is received.
Just as advertised :) Exactly what I needed for IRLP work with non-DTMF mics! 73 de KJ4WLH
Excellent app! Love it! Does EXACTLY what it says, and does it well!
Perfect for hamradio use. Love it. Works great. AE7HF
Works better than some of the other apps I tested but hardly ever gets the entire code right, misses some and doubles others, get an incorect digit every now and then, HTC Wildfire S.
Works as stated.
This is the only app that actually works. Well worth the $ :-)
